The '''Nyambo''', or '''Ragwe''', are a Bantu ethnic and linguistic group based in the [[Karagwe]] District of [[Kagera Region]] in far northwestern [[Tanzania]]. In 2003 the Nyambo population was estimated to number 400,000.<ref>http://www.ethnologue.com/show_country.asp?name=TZ</ref>
