'''Poolla Tirupati Raju''' (3 September 1904 – 1992) was an Indian writer, philosopher, academic and a former professor of Jaswant College, Jodhpur (present day [[Jai Narain Vyas University]].<ref name="Notification">{{cite web | url=http://www.pib.nic.in/archive/docs/DVD_03/ACC%20NO%20011-BR/RAS-1958-01-29-3936.pdf | title=Notification | publisher=The Gazette of India | date=1958 | accessdate=4 March 2016}}</ref> He was the author of several books, both in English and [[Telugu language|Telugu]], on Indian philosophy and literature.<ref name="Raju, P. T. (Poolla Tirupati)">{{cite web | url=http://www.worldcat.org/identities/lccn-n50-54421/ | title=Raju, P. T. (Poolla Tirupati) | publisher=WorldCat identities | date=2016 | accessdate=4 March 2016}}</ref><ref name="P. T. Raju (1904–1992)">{{cite web | url=https://www.librarything.com/author/rajupt | title=P. T. Raju (1904–1992) | publisher=LibraryThing | date=2016 | accessdate=4 March 2016}}</ref> His publications include ''Structural Depths of Indian Thought''<ref name="Structural Depths of Indian Thought">{{cite book | url=http://www.goodreads.com/book/show/5861164-structural-depths-of-indian-thought | title=Structural Depths of Indian Thought | publisher=State University of New York Press | author=Poola Tirupati Raju | year=1985 | pages=599 | isbn=9780887061394}}</ref> ''Telugu Literature'',<ref name="Telugu Literature">{{cite book | url=https://books.google.ae/books/about/Telugu_Literature.html?id=M48OAAAAYAAJ&redir_esc=y | title=Telugu Literature | publisher=Internat. Book House | author=Poola Tirupati Raju | year=1944 | pages=154}}</ref> ''The Philosophical Traditions of India''<ref name="The Philosophical Traditions of India">{{cite book | url=http://www.worldcat.org/title/philosophical-traditions-of-india/oclc/482322 | title=The Philosophical Traditions of India | publisher=University of Pittsburgh Press | author=Poola Tirupati Raju | year=1972 | pages=256 | isbn=9780822911050}}</ref> ''Introduction to Comparative Philosophy''<ref name="Introduction to Comparative Philosophy">{{cite book | url=http://www.worldcat.org/title/introduction-to-comparative-philosophy/oclc/372601 | title=Introduction to Comparative Philosophy | publisher=University of Nebraska Press | author=Poola Tirupati Raju | year=1962 | pages=364 | OCLC=372601}}</ref> and Idealistic Thought of India.<ref name="Idealistic Thought of India">{{cite book | url=http://www.worldcat.org/title/idealistic-thought-of-india/oclc/3615962 | title=Idealistic Thought of India | publisher=Harvard University Press | author=Poola Tirupati Raju | year=1953 | pages=454 | OCLC=3615962}}</ref> He was the editor of ''The Concept of Man: A Study in Comparative Philosophy'', written by [[Sarvepalli Radhakrishnan]].<ref name="The Concept of Man: A Study in Comparative Philosophy">{{cite book | url=https://www.amazon.in/dp/1258007541 | title=The Concept of Man: A Study in Comparative Philosophy | publisher=Literary Licensing | author=Sarvepalli Radhakrishnan (Author), Poola Tirupati Raju (Editor) | year=2011 | pages=382 | isbn=9781258007546}}</ref> The Government of India awarded him the third highest civilian honour of the [[Padma Bhushan]], in 1958, for his contributions to Literature and education.<ref name="Padma Awards">{{cite web | url=http://mha.nic.in/sites/upload_files/mha/files/LST-PDAWD-2013.pdf | title=Padma Awards | publisher=Ministry of Home Affairs, Government of India | date=2016 | accessdate=3 January 2016}}</ref>

